### Description
Target: NXP Kinetis Freedom FRDM-K64F
Toolchain: GCC-ARM 7 2017-q4-major
Tool: PlatformIO IDE
Mbed OS Version: 5.8.2

The FRDM-K64F as an SPI Slave always receives 0xFF from the `read()` function (although `receive()` works as expected).

Steps to reproduce the problem:

Freedom FRDM-K64F as SPI Slave:
```c++
#include "mbed.h"
#include <vector>
 
 int main()
 {
     SPISlave device(PTD2, PTD3, PTD1, PTD0);
     device.frequency(100000);
     device.format(8,0);
 
     std::vector<int> dataBlock;
 
     while ( !device.receive() );
 
     while ( device.receive() )
     {
             dataBlock.push_back( device.read() );
     }
 
     printf("Got data!: ");
 
     for (int i = 0; i < dataBlock.size(); i++)
     {
         printf("%d ", dataBlock[i]);
     }
     printf("\n"); // Output is "Got data!: 255 255 255 255 255 255"

     return 0;
}
```
I used UBlox C027 (another board running mbed) as SPI Master

UBlox C027 as SPI Master:
```c++
#include "mbed.h"
#include <vector>

int main()
{
    SPI spi(P1_24, P1_23, P1_20, P1_21);
 
    spi.frequency(100000);
    spi.format(8,0);
 
    std::vector<int> dataBlock = {1,2,3,4,5,6,7};
 
    for (int i = 0; i < dataBlock.size(); i++)
    {
        spi.write( dataBlock[i] );
    }

     return 0;
}
```

